==English==

=== Pronunciation ===

[[SAMPA]]: [kaI"a:zm@s]


=== [[Noun]] ===

An inversion of the relationship between the elements of phrases, e.g. ''To stop too fearful, and too faint to go'' -- [[Goldmith]]. Used especially in [[classical language]]s, e.g. ''haec queritur, stupet haec (this woman complains, this one gapes)'' -- [[Ovid]], ''[[Ars Amatoria]]'', 1.124


=== [[Etymology]] ===

Latin ''chiasmus'' from Greek ''chiasmos'', from ''chiazein'' (to mark with a chi), from [[chi]], written &chi;.